A: Pours a super hazy, pale orange in color with a one inch, frothy paper white head with fair retention. Thick white lacing throughout.
S: Big aromas of citrus and tropical fruits including grapefruit, orange, melons, peach, passionfruit, and guava.
T: Huge juice bomb!! Starts off with big notes of grapefruit, orange rind, and melons followed by light notes of peach, passionfruit, and pineapple. Finishes with a nice lingering piney, resinous hop bitterness.
F: Medium bodied, velvety smooth, pillowy mouthfeel with light carbonation. Slight dryness on the finish.
O: Overall, this is an amazing DIPA. Super juicy, but well balanced with the perfect level of hop bitterness. Artfully crafted. Wish I could drink this every day! 786 charactersBeerGuy8315, May 02, 2017
