4.04/5  rDev -9.8%look: 4 | smell: 5 | taste: 3.5 | feel: 4 |  overall: 4The beer looks like a standard New England IPA. Light yellow color with the cloudiness you expect. There was very little head, however. What head was there was white and dissipated quickly.
The smell is wonderful. Heavy notes of orange and pineapple with some floral characteristics and a light grassiness. No heat on the nose. Just wonderful for a double IPA.
The flavor falls a bit flat. Very little complexity.  Light orange pith with piney finish. Not a lot of heat up front but after the pine goes away, your mouth is just left with the alcohol burns.
The body is nice and full with a decent compliment of carbonation. There could be a bit more carbonation bite though.
I find that I don't share the common view of Trillium. Every beer I have from them has one great quality and one not great quality. Is usually a fight between nose and flavor. This time the nose was great and the flavor didn't follow. They do good beer but its not worth the price. 960 charactersTheBeerCarl, Apr 18, 2017
