4.5/5  rDev +0.4%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.5My first hoppy Trillium, poured from the can into my Trillium Sevilla glass.
Great looking beer, hazy orange, with a really nice, fluffy head.
The smell is pure, unadultarated tropical juice. Passionfruit and pineapple dominate, and the end of the sniff is sweet.
The taste is as tropical as the nose, massive pineapple and passionfruit waves crash on your tongue. The fruityness is follwed by a tremendously balanced hop bitterness, and just a hint of booze. The lingering hoppy finish is spectacular.
Mouthfeel is everything I read about and hoped for. Soft and airy, but with good body and perfect carbonation.
My first hoppy Trillium, and wow, what a tropical delight. Great balance, just the right amount of warming booze. Superb. 740 charactersJamFuel, Mar 22, 2017
