4.29/5  rDev -4.2%look: 4.25 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.25 | feel: 4 |  overall: 4.25Poured into a Duvel tulip.  Bottom of can says 01/19/17.
A- Pours a murky medium amber color with a 1/2 inch off-white head that retains well before becoming a thick ring around the edge of the glass and a full sheet of sheer surface foam.
S- Very big melon note off this one as well as some apricot and peach.
T- The flavor is more resinous and has some pine quality to it but still pretty fruity as well.  More citrus rather than stone fruit though with some orange and grapefruit-y tartness.  Bitterness is more pronounced than you usually get with these NE IPAs.
M- Soft in the body but with a moderate sharpness from the hops.  Medium carbonation and a body leaning toward the lighter side.
O- The ABV is expertly concealed and the flavor profile is cohesive, but it's a bit dry for my tastes.  A great beer but not outstanding within the Trillium portfolio for me. 875 charactersImmortale25, Feb 05, 2017
