4.52/5  rDev +0.9%look: 4.25 | smell: 4.75 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.25 |  overall: 4.516oz can.
Pours murky gold.with an inch of white fluff. Retention and lacing is minimal.
Aromatics are pungently hoppy, abound with juicy citrus. Candied grapefruit, tangerine, pineapple, and peach. On the chewier side of medium bodied with a resinous, tacky mouthfeel. Buckets of tropical fruit on the palate. Heavier on the grapefruit with zesty citrus packing a whallop. Finishes long with plenty of dank, fruity hops and a firm bitterness.
This is the Trillium that has more of everything that all their hop-forward beers are known for. Killer. 550 charactersbrewandbbq, Jan 22, 2017
4.5/5  rDev +0.4%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.5Arober22, Jan 21, 2017
4.4/5  rDev -1.8%look: 5 | smell: 4.25 | taste: 4.25 | feel: 4.75 |  overall: 4.5If we're being honest, I was getting a little bored of Trillium's offerings towards the end of last year. Like many here, I found my palate was less and less wowed with each hop bomb as they all blend into that dominantly hazy, tropical and vinous taste before finishing dry. I wasn't complaining, but I wasn't wowed. This last month, however, has been like a new leaf. Pow Pow, DDH Congress/Stillings, Pinot Gris Dialed In... and now this huge return. I must say expectations were massive going in here. After a seven month wait, I knew the Trill boys must have really honed this one in. And fucking hell did they. 
Pours a murky golden orange. Mango juice. Smell doesn't spring out of the glass like Scaled Up or their DDH offerings but the citrus and alcohol presence let's you know this guy isn't mucking about. The second you sip this, you can feel the Lupulin presence tickle your gums and cheeks for ten seconds. They obviously went wayyyy overboard on the hop additions, and I for one am NOT complaining.
Tastes like underripe peach, Meyer lemon, dried apricot, green apple skin, and lots and lots of hop pellets. Resinous, sticky, mealy. Full bodied is an understatement, but it maintains a very nice and bright carbonation. Doesn't hide the 9.3% whatsoever but jeez this is hard to put down. So glad I have another 100+ ounces in the fridge to enjoy as it evolves over the next few weeks. More of this please! 1,421 charactersbarsonthetrak, Jan 21, 2017
