4.27/5  rDev -4.7%look: 4 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.5Thanks to SadMachine for this bottle, as I try to ferret out the appeal of this newish brewery. 750ML bottle split with my wife. And I dig the labels - reminds me of 1776 Boston for some reason. 
The pour is watery orange juice run through CO2. The aroma is a non-dainty face slap of tropical fruit with lots of Florida oranges. Hard to understand that much fruit without a Renaissance Festival style fruit stomp during the boil. 
Heavy Mettle - can confirm this is good. The orange, mango, & peach that catapult out of the glass is simply ridiculous. Bitter citrus rides the mid-palate along with a sweet, candied backbone moving into a clean, Invisible Man-style finish. Almost nothing lingers on the palate until the next loving sip. Juicy - which I usually don’t use as a complement, but I do here. No apparent alcohol, which makes it easy to slug as Tang. 
My second Trillium & now I begin to see the hype, which I didn’t the first go-round. Drinkable, fruity as a strawberry gelato, & with enough bitterness to let me know I’m not drinking Fanta. Excellent brew. 1,077 charactersmaximum12, Jul 30, 2016
