Consumed 7/6/16
A: Tangerine gold - so stupidly turbid, beyond hazy and more like a soup - pours with a medium sized, white head, fades to a wispy cap but retains a medium collar, leaves some nice spots and streaks of lacing
S: Like opening a bag of hop pellets - straight-up hop juice, hop resin, and leafy hops - waves of citrus, with tangerine, orange, and grapefruit flesh, juice - some pine resin and pine needles in addition to the leafy cones - decidedly dank, even more resin and some spicy herbal aromas - peach and stone fruit - tropical with some rich pineapple, mango, guava, passion fruit - some pale malts at the base
T: An assault of hops - big, sticky citrus with some orange and grapefruit flesh and oil - herbal and vaguely spicy, leafy hops - resinous hops and resinous pine, with a touch of pine needles, hint of grass - more citrusy/leafy in the taste than expected, with fewer tropical notes compared to the aroma - some fleshy peach, pineapple, and passion fruit - more straight-up grapefruit in the finish - some dry, pale, crackery malts at the base with a touch of booze
M: On the full side of medium, smooth and a bit fuzzy like many Trillium IPAs, lightly oily but it actually finishes dry and mostly clean, with some booze
O: It's like that Metallica shirt with the knife coming out of the toilet... except with hops
Heavy Mettle is so brutal it could be on Metalocalypse. It builds on a few things that Mettle does right and just makes everything substantially better with an absurd amount of hops. 1,574 charactersangrybabboon, Jul 06, 2016
