4.45/5  rDev -0.7%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4 |  overall: 4.5Bottled 6/15/16
Pours a nice fluffy creamy 1 finger head with thick froth in the middle, fades at a med pace with nice soapy lacing, milk shake murky pale straw tangerine orange color.
Nose explodes with citrus and fruit, big tangerine and orange peel, some grapefruit pith, juicy peach and nectarine flesh, with a little fruity bubblegum, touch of melon rind and maybe a hint of grape must, clementine, tangelo, and lots of nice citrus juice, and maybe even a faint mango and tropical pineapple thing, with a hint of creamy juicy malt underneath.
Taste brings a touch of piney note, with dank resin, a bit earthy, not too bad, quickly into citrus rind, a big rind and sweet orange peel, tangerine clementine citrus again, some juice and plenty of rind, with some pith as well, into some mild peachy nectarine like stone fruit, some grapefruit as well, and again faint mango and pineapple like tropical notes,back into some orange fruit juice packets that you rip apart when peeling the fruit. A mild soft creamy sweet-ish malt underneath, creamy wheat, almost chewy. Finish is dry, a little creamy wheat still, plenty more bitter grapefruit pith, orange rind, and mild tropical notes.
Mouth is med to fuller bod, a hint of booze on the back end, creamy wheat, carb is a bit on the lighter side.
Overall pretty nice, not their best but def a good one. Glad to see so many good ones from them as they really seemed to have ramped up their game, and finally getting to the good hops (non mosaic). 1,498 charactersjlindros, Jun 30, 2016
