3.84/5  rDev -14.3%look: 4 | smell: 3.75 | taste: 3.75 | feel: 4 |  overall: 4bottle dated 6/15/16. pale milky yellow color with a dense white head, nice retention and a bit of lacing. 
thought the nose on this was a little weak, theres a hint of pineapple, grassyness & alcohol. maybe Im crazy but honestly I thought the smell of the fort point ales popped way more than this, which shouldnt be the case considering this one is in the higher range of abv. 
nice fruity hops up front, and a solid bitterness on the finish - but the alcohol is apparent, especially as the beer warms, which definitely hurts the flavor profile. the combination of astringent alcohol, bitter pine and a mineraly finish is pretty brutal. feel is slightly thinner and less creamy than the other trillium ales ive had.
overall, given that this beer is only 9.3% its pretty disappointing that the alcohol is so apparent. maybe im being overly critical, maybe my palate is shot, maybe im crazy idk. I first tried this beer about a week ago and decided not to write a review because I wasnt impressed and I thought the booze was more predominant than any of the flavors I expected to experience. for me this didnt live up to the hype at all, and it was definitely my least favorite from trillium. but like I said I had two bottles dated the 15th so both were consumed within 2 weeks...makes me kind of sad because I havent tried a trillium beer yet that wasnt at the very least excellent, and I think this one is pretty poor. 1,424 charactersHyptochrons, Jun 29, 2016
