4.54/5  rDev +1.3%look: 4.75 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.25 |  overall: 4.756/15/16 bottling date; 10 days old
A: Pours a super cloudy pale orange. Enormous frothy light tan head. Amazing head retention with thick walls of lacing. Basically perfect.
S: Huge citrus aroma with a mixture of tropical fruits. Oranges, grapefruits and pineapple primarily I'd say. Very pungent. Even get some melons in there.
T: Very similar to the aroma. Big sharp citrus and tropical fruits. Huge herbal spiciness. Nice wave of bitterness on the back end with a long drying citrus peel finish.
M: Medium-heavy with a very soft, dry mouthfeel.
O: Great DIPA. Huge hoppiness without too much bitterness. Dry crisp and refreshing. A perfectly amped-up version of their normal IPA lineup. Juicy as hell. 709 charactersDope, Jun 26, 2016
4.65/5  rDev +3.8%look: 4.75 | smell: 4.75 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.75 |  overall: 4.75Poured from a 750 ml bottle into a pint glass. Thanks Steve for hooking me up with this one. 
Pours a super hazy, freshly squeezed orange juice orange color with a big white head that reduces slowly to leave good lacing and retention. One of the haziest, nicest looking Trillium's I've ever seen!
Aromas are juicy, tropical, fruity, orange creamsicle, pineapple juice, grapefruit. Taste matches the nose with plenty of orange creamsicle, citrus, tons of tropical fruits, light bitterness on the finish. Easy drinker, the ABV is not apparent at all, medium body and carbonation. 
