4.41/5  rDev -1.6%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.75 | taste: 4.25 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.25Poured from a 750ml bottle into tulip glasses:
Appearance: pours a super murky and hazy orange-pink color, with a huge, lingering white head. The head sticks around for a few minutes, leaving sticky, spotted lacing. Beautiful looking beer....the epitome of a Trillium ale.
Aroma: hop aroma pours out of the bottle the second the cap comes off. Layers upon layers of citrus, grapefruit, and a fair amount of bitterness come out. Doesn't smell boozy, but there is a little sweetness on the scent too.
Taste: super duper hoppy and fresh tasting. It does have that raw hop flavor that comes through in a lot of Trillium beers. Packs a ton of grapefruit and pineapple in there, with a little bit of fruity sweetness in addition to the bitterness and hop flavor. It's not my favorite Trillium IPA, but it's pretty damn good.
Feel: very thick and full-bodied, it puts the "heavy" in Heavy Mettle. This is super thick and sticky.
Overall: this was another excellent DIPA from Trillium. Seek it out, and wrap yourself in hops. 1,022 charactersTheElectricOne, May 21, 2016
