4.23/5  rDev -5.6%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4 | feel: 4.25 |  overall: 4.25A:  Very hazy, finger of white head which leaves behind some impressive lacing.  If you poured this into a "normal" drinking glass without any head I could see myself mistaking this for a glass of juice.
S:  Tropical frutiness.  Unlike the appearance there is just enough of a bitter undertone for me to know I'm not smelling a juice.
T:  Less tropical and juicy than some other Trillium offerings I've had.  The hope flavor is nice here and there is a balance between the bitterness and fruit notes.
F:  Theres a certain thickness to this that I don't usually get in IPAs.  Not on the level of a stout, but it has substance. 
O:  For most breweries this is where I'd say they've really stepped up their game and this is fantastic.  This is a Trillium IPA though, and while great, it isn't quite on the level of some of their other beers, even some of those in regular rotation.  Basically, if you're like me and Trillium is on your commute home, its worth picking up a bottle or two, but not worth going out of your way for.  If you don't have regular access to the brewery and you have a chance to get one of these, be it through trade or whatever, do it. 1,157 charactersPierre_Pressure, May 21, 2016
