4.94/5  rDev +10.3%look: 4.75 | smell: 5 | taste: 5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 5My favorite beer. Accordingly, I'd probably disregard everything I'm about to say, because I'm too emotional to be taken seriously. This beer is possessed of towering, stupid fruit, y'all; a hazy, luminous monster, crowding the glass at the juice zoo. Hot-house orange nectar sweet meets hot-boxing-your-friends'-mom's-station-wagon bitter, and has a fight, a dumb fight, over which one is best and they both win.
Some things I thought of while drinking Heavy Mettle
- the youtube clip of the scene in Spider Man where Randy Savage goes 'BONE SAW IS READY' over and over and over, but, like, as a hop profile.
- being beaten up by a gang of enormous, delicious clementines.
- If the drum fill from 'In The Air Tonight' by Phil Collins were a beer.
- (Which is basically the same as) If former Celtic Kevin Garnett were a beer. 
- Why, if it possible to make this beer, more people aren't doing it.
This is the beer I drank to say goodbye to Prince. This is the beer I'd ask for if I knew the world was going to end. I'll serve this beer at my wedding if I have one and it is available. This beer is my child. My juicy, explosive child. 1,137 charactersHankSingle, May 16, 2016
