4.57/5  rDev +2%look: 4.25 | smell: 4.75 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.75 |  overall: 4.5Bottled 5/3/2016. You dudes remember Mettle? Meet its kicked-up older brother.
Appearance - The appearance is super hazy, like freshly-squeezed pineapple juice. Of all the hazy Trillium IPAs I've had, this very well may be the haziest. With that added opacity comes a darker shade of orange as well compared to Mettle. 
Aroma - Whereas the nose on Mettle was a playful combination between fruity and piney, Heavy Mettle is pretty much all fruit, especially the peach. The Galaxy hops are the star here and shine beyond even the Amarillo.
Taste - The flavor aggressive and toes the boundary between smooth tropical flavors and a somewhat harsher hop bite. At first the peach and grapefruit dominate, but as the beer sits, there is a noticeable vegetal quality in the finish, like when you taste your gravity sample of a homebrewed IPA. Just that raw hop bitterness flavor. It comes and goes though, so it isn't overpowering - moreso a lingering feeling. Tons of hop flavor through and through though.
Mouthfeel - The mouthfeel is moderately heavy-bodied with good carbonation. Bucking the trend from the other Trillium IPAs I've had recently, this one has a really substantial body to it and good carbonation to really drive the flavors. Perfectly textured.
Closing Arguments - Overall, this may be in the running for favorite IPA from these guys, but honestly it's a very tight race. A definite step up from Mettle, but a whole different animal for sure. 1,459 charactersnhindian, May 15, 2016
