4.61/5  rDev +2.9%look: 4.75 | smell: 5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.25 |  overall: 4.5Poured from a 64 oz growler into a tulip glass with about a fingers worth of head which settles down into a soft glaze on top. Appearance is so cloudy, hazy, and thick with a nice orange juice colored hue. The nose on this beer pops out as soon as the cap is twisted like a dank cloud! Hints of sappy pine, summer fruit like ripe nectarines and peaches jump out along with some ripe melon.  The nose may be the best part of this beer, and that's not to slight the taste portion, it just really catapults into your nose like not many others. 
Tart citrus and peach jump out across the palette, with a thin mouthfeel, though medium bodied. You can really discern the booze factor on this one, though the initial pour may have been from a growler not totally refrigerated after pick up. Either way, its so drinkable and smooth, you almost forget its over 9%, and that can sneak up on you quick! Overall this beer is extremely pleasant, from look and nose to taste. While I still hold Vicinity in highest regard, this was one HELL of a beer! 1,038 charactersSolebird23, May 13, 2016
