4.93/5  rDev +10%look: 4.75 | smell: 4.75 | taste: 5 | feel: 5 |  overall: 5Grabbed a growler. Three days old.
A- heavy mettle pours a patented New England fluorescent orange with golden hues and a frothy white head of foam. As I always desire from a great IPA/DIPA, the brew glows in the glass and literally displays the Galaxy and Amarillo hop glow in used to seeing
S- orange juice in a glass! A burst of freshly squeezed juice is bundled with pineapple, tangerine, and guava. While congress st was predominantly grape fruit, HM is the fresh tropical flavors that I love. Not bitter, just sweet and mouth watering
T- nailed it. My first juice nuclear bomb. I was hoping the Galaxy and Amarillo would dominate and bundle into a juice smoothie on roids. While not overwhelming thick, the tropical flavors have no bitterness and just an unbelievable taste. What a combination of flavor that can be very hard to find. 
M- carbonated and flavor piercing, heavy mettle feels fantastic. Not enough can be said about the feel and mouth watering experience this causes. Most drinkable 9.3% brew ever
O- maybe tree house juice machine could battle this but not even Julius can compare. This tropical profile is the literal depiction of a juice bomb. Trillium literally created a profile that is not easy to duplicate. One of the best DIPAS that I've ever had in terms of a tropical brew 1,308 characterslovindahops, May 11, 2016
