4.43/5  rDev -1.1%look: 4.25 | smell: 4.25 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.5Pours an opaque golden orange color with a small white head. Leaves some nice cobweb lacing. 
The aroma is pretty tropical, with notes of mangoes and pineapple. Also get a slight green pepper aroma. Mild amounts of citrus. 
If Mettle is a juice bomb, then this is a juice apocalypse. Sweet orange juice, grapefruit, mangoes, honeydew melon, and peaches are all thrown into a blender. A blender made out of pineapples. There's also a touch of bitter pine on the finish. Has a decent caramel malt backbone that's subtle but present. 
The feel is medium bodied with moderate-at-best carbonation. Very creamy and smooth, and the alcohol is nicely hidden. No lingering bitterness to speak of. 
Overall, an excellent DIPA that does everything Mettle does, but better. It's fairly well balanced and despite being the juiciest thing since Beyonce's ass, it's not overly sweet. Just a great, great beer. 898 charactersScaryEd, May 06, 2016
