4.49/5  rDev +0.2%look: 4.25 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.5L- semi hazy yellow.  actually both lighter and clearer than i expected.  foggy but not dense.  head is white and strong with thick lacing as it subsides.  
S- mangoes, passion fruit.  basically trop fruit city. smells awesome but doesn't necessarily pop with as much intensity as it could.
T-fruit for days.  orange sherbet.  candied mango from trail mix.  mellon.  grapefruit flesh, peel and pith.  herbaceous and piney dankness follows the fruit and brings a soft but firm bitterness.  the fruit pops back up after only a second of absence, and joins the green aspects seamlessly.  they both linger for days as one overall flavor.
F- medium soft cream.  some heat but nothing to suggest 9.3  
O- fantastic stuff.  i don't usually fuck with +9% ipas but when theyre done right, theyre done right.  intense fruit couple with the right amout of green dankness.  the hops never clashed, and it never got sweet.  bomb shit 924 charactersmeson13, Nov 12, 2015
