Appearance:  A two finger head was poured that reduced to a thin layer.  It is a pale yellow orange color with great clarity and vision of bubbles coming up through the glass.  Frothy lacing down the glass as the beer was drank. 
Smell:  Tropical, candied stone fruit, citrus, resiny pine, herbal, spicy, and floral hops followed by caramel and toasted malts.  Some alcohol in there too.
Taste:  Awesome hop flavor with balancing malt bill, light to medium bitterness, and light boozy alcohol.
Mouthfeel:  Smooth, medium to full bodied, light to medium bitterness, a little boozy alcohol, and medium carbonation. 
Overall:  This beer eluded me for some time.  Not anymore and happy to have enjoyed it.  Looking forward to the next batch. 790 charactersFlounder57, Nov 07, 2015
