Very hazy yellow-orange, billowy head with good retention and lacing.
Smells like freshly cut pineapple, including the skin. Not the most aromatic IPA I've run into, but nice.
Very fruity.  Peaches, lighter notes of pineapple.
A bit low on carbonation, but clean with a long fruity linger and minimal bitterness.
TBH, I've been a bit disappointed with most Trillium IPAs, finding them to have something of a vegetal off-flavor, particularly as they warm.  This one, however, has none of that and is pure deliciousness.  I don't know if it's just a matter of being fresher, or being kept nice and cold by being shipped through Polar Vortex 2015, but this is legit. 686 characterskscaldef, Jan 13, 2015
