4.2/5  rDev -6.3%look: 4.75 | smell: 4 | taste: 4.25 | feel: 4 |  overall: 4.25Bomber into a Sam Adams glass.  Didn't share with anyone ;-)
Absolutely beautiful pour.  Pineapple juice color with a bit of haze that makes it appear to glow.  Decent, thin head.
Aroma is a blast of sweet tropical fruits.  I was actually pouring mai tais for guests as I was drinking this, and this beer smells a bit like the beer version of a mai tai.
Great, complex flavor.  Pineapple and mango dominate.  The relatively dense mouthfeel really brings out these flavors, and makes them sort of chewy.  There is a slight onion and boozy bite near the finish, which I didn't really care for, but it didn't spoil the experience.  That goes away quick and it finishes a bit sticky and sweet.
Very nice offering once again from Trillium. 738 charactersstonermouse, Jan 02, 2015
