A: Pours a light pale/pineapple juice-like color, with a half finger of bright white head.  Very good retention and some streaks of lacing.  
S: Citrus (grapefruit, orange), dankness, rose petal, tangerine, a little light malt for backbone.  
T: Citrus, pineapple, dankness, some light malt notes (rye bread), with mild pithy bitterness on a long finish.  
M: Medium body and carbonation.  Feels soft, and alcohol is extremely well hidden.  
