A - Hazy orange color with some excellent lace retention
S - Amazing citrus explosion. Grapefruits, oranges, mangos, limes. Just overpowering and juicy as anything
T - Follows the nose to a T. The galaxy hops shine here. They dominate this brew. You get the slightest grassy finish on the palate. The ABV flys under the radar. I could crush this brew but it's meant to be enjoyed slowly :-)
M - Medium body, medium carb, slightly bitter on the palate
O - As close to a perfect 5 as you can get. The only thing holding it back is maybe the slightest lack of balance as it's a huge citrus bomb. That's what I enjoy but in the context of a perfect DIPA, that's what I found to be missing. Whatever, it's incredibly exceptional. 753 charactersrjp217, Aug 20, 2014
